menu "Example Configurations"
    config LAKESHARK_HEADLESS
        bool "Headless build (UART console, no display/GUI)"
        default n
        help
            Build the headless variant: boot straight into the radio backend and
            a UART console instead of the Brookesia touch GUI. Shares the same
            radio core (P25 / FM / ADS-B). Leave OFF for the GUI build.

    config EXAMPLE_ENABLE_SD_CARD
        bool "Enable SD Card"
        default n
        help
            Enabling this option will initialize the SD card, so the SD card needs to be inserted into the slot. Additionally, if using the Video Player example, an MJPEG format video must be saved on the SD card.
endmenu